    "lyrics": {
      "text": "O_ _ Lord, though Thou didst stand be-fore__ the tri-bu--nal, en-dur-ing judg-ment at Pi-late’s hands, Thou didst not de-part from Thy Fa---ther, seat-ed with Him on Thy throne a-bove. And Thou didst rise__ from the dead, O Friend of man most mer-ci-ful, free-ing the world from the bit-ter bond--age of the al-i-en and en--e--my."
